i'm really sad right now, seeing how Mr.shapiro recently past away. He was so awesome. He was by far one of the best people around. He was kind, good hearted, and always there. Gracious is the only way to describe him. I can't believe that he's gone, but in a way he's still here. His legacy will forever live throughout the halls of LHS. And tonight i went to the gathering at his house and it was really nice. I got a chance to meet his wife and she is really nice, but the funny thing is that she was so strong about everything. I didn't see her cry at all and she just focused on all the positive aspects of Mr. Shapiro's life. They were so lucky to have each other, two amazing people.
     She showed me the pictures in the livingroom of the trip to hawaii that they took and up till that point i had managed to keep my tears in side, but when i saw his face and how happy he was i just broke down. He was so happy, he was supposed to come right back after treatment and surgery and stuff but then this happened. How come the best people in life are taken so soon? I think that these people are put here to guide us, but when they are taken away it opens our eyes to the things around us and reveals  the reality that we need knowledge of. 

                         Mr.shapiro...........Rest In Peace
forever you will live on.........in our hearts.......we'll miss you



although you are gone,
your legacy lives on,
never forgotten,
yet taken forgranted.......
but you made us happy,
you made us laugh.
your purpose on earth,
was to guide our paths.......
you taught us by choice,
not by default,
you did a good job,
no matter ho you felt,
you are deeply missed,
your legacy lives on,
you are deeply missed,
now that you're gone...........
but you will never be forgotten...................never
